task_description: Facing the building to your South-East (approx. 140°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the front-left position (move_id 2) will provide a closer, better angle to view the full height of the target building, helping me make a more accurate height estimation.

Instead of rotating in place where the target building isn't visible, I'll move forward (move_id 1) to a closer position, which should allow me to see the South-East building clearly for height estimation.
Based on the typical scale of residential buildings, estimating the target as a 6-story structure with ~3 meters per floor gives a total height of 18.0 meters.
